data.title: What! Veteran Bollywood actress Bindu names Zeenat Aman as the biggest 'flirt' of 70s; says 'sorry' to the 'Don' actress
data.meta_description: Known for her dance sequences and vamp roles, veteran actress Bindu recently was asked to name one 70s actress who used to flirt with their co-stars the most. During a rapid-fire session with an entertainment portal, the film 'Main Hoon Na' actress stunned everyone with her answer as she named her former co-star Zeenat Aman. Yes, you heard that right. However, after naming her, she scrunched her face and apologized to the 'Don' actress. Both actresses have worked together in films like 'Prem Shastra' (1974), 'Chor Ke Ghar Chor' (1978), 'Laawaris' (1981), and others. For more news and updates, stay tuned to ETimes.
